aded method. Graceful degradation: if SparseEncoder fails, fall back to dense-only.\\n- Add test: SparseEncoderTest.java — test tokenization, domain term normalization, sparse vector generation\\n- Update PineconeClientTest.java — test upsert/query include sparse vectors when present, and fall back gracefully when absent\",\n  \"requiredChecks\": [\n    \"lint\",\n    \"typecheck\",\n    \"unit\",\n    \"build\"\n  ]\n}\n\nYou are the first agent to work on this step.\nImplement the changes described above, run checks to verify, and fix any issues before handing off.\nBe thorough — the next agent will review your work and should find it correct.\n\nPrior observations from earlier steps (address if they fall within this step's scope):\n- [MEDIUM] step 1 OpenRouterAiProvider.java: The retry loop calls `callOpenRouter` twice on parse failure, consuming 2 rate-limit tokens instead of 1. For a rate limit of 30/min this is unlikely to matter, but could be refined if needed in a future step\n\nWhen done, explain what you reviewed, what you changed (if anything), and your assessment.\n\nEnd with:\nVerdict: approve  — if the step is complete and correct, no more changes needed\nVerdict: changes_made  — if you made fixes or improvements\nVerdict: replan_needed  — if the step is structurally impossible to complete as planned and needs controller-managed replanning"}],"timestamp":1774812338698}}
